│ of whether dependencies have been initialized, triggering the assertion when hasValidDependencies() is false. A │
│ safe fix is to avoid calling incrementUnscheduledDeps when dependencies are invalid; for control edges without  │
│ computed deps, we can treat them as having zero deps and only enqueue if the bundle is ready, without touching  │
│ the counters. I'll inspect further down in schedule() to patch the DecrUnsched condition to require valid       │
│ dependencies before incrementing, and handle the IsControl case by only enqueuing when the bundle is ready.     │
