│ THOUGHT: The remaining crash indicates incrementUnscheduledDeps is still being invoked when a specific          │
│ ScheduleData instance lacks valid dependency info, even if an outer entity reports validity. To robustly        │
│ prevent the abort while preserving behavior, I will make ScheduleData::incrementUnscheduledDeps tolerate        │
│ invalid dependency state by early-returning without modifying counters when dependencies are not valid. This    │
│ prevents the assertion and avoids corrupting scheduling counters.                                               │
│                                                                                                                 │
│ ```bash                                                                                                         │
│ sed -i '4773,4776s/assert(hasValidDependencies()) &&/if (!hasValidDependencies()) return UnscheduledDeps; \n    │
│ /' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch                                              │
│ ```                                                                                                             │
